00:30:03,735 --> 00:30:06,044
We changed the kitchen location

500
00:30:06,438 --> 00:30:08,988
to be Oogway's peach tree.

501
00:30:09,408 --> 00:30:13,158
The peach is a symbol of immortality
in Chinese culture,

502
00:30:14,379 --> 00:30:17,809
peach blossom and peach tree leaves

503
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:19,659
are used in Taoist magic.

504
00:30:19,918 --> 00:30:23,457
The wood of the peach tree
is said to ward off evil.

505
00:30:24,022 --> 00:30:26,212
So, in our mythology,

506
00:30:26,591 --> 00:30:28,610
it was Cogway
who planted the peach tree...

507
00:30:29,895 --> 00:30:32,795
..a thousand years ago
when he first came to China.

508
00:30:33,265 --> 00:30:36,605
And his staff is made
from the wood of the peach tree.

509
00:30:37,135 --> 00:30:40,065
The peach tree is the place
that overlooks the valley,

510
00:30:40,539 --> 00:30:42,209
and is this very significant place.

511
00:30:42,507 --> 00:30:45,057
One other thing to mention
is that Oogway brings light.

512
00:30:45,477 --> 00:30:48,317
It's a moment of enlightenment
between Oogway and Po.

513
00:30:48,780 --> 00:30:51,820
So it was a really cool visual thing

514
00:30:52,317 --> 00:30:55,307
to have him bring the lantern
and leave light behind.

515
00:30:55,787 --> 00:30:58,187
It also was a good transition.

516
00:30:58,590 --> 00:31:01,840
He's in the same color language,
blue and a bit of orange.

517
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:05,821
We go from the blue of the night sky
and the orange of the lantern

518
00:31:06,365 --> 00:31:10,285
to the golden orange of Tai Lung's eyes

519
00:31:10,902 --> 00:31:11,869
in the cut to our first
big action set piece.

520
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,649
in the cut to our first
big action set piece.

521
00:31:15,507 --> 00:31:17,377
While we're in the land of color,

522
00:31:17,709 --> 00:31:20,669
this whole sequence was designed
to be a battle between

523
00:31:21,146 --> 00:31:25,126
blue, Tai Lungs color,
and red, the power color.

524
00:31:25,751 --> 00:31:28,441
If you watch the scene
a couple of times, you'll notice that

525
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:31,226
as Tai Lung wins each level,

526
00:31:31,623 --> 00:31:34,583
‘cause the thing is designed
like a video game with levels,

527
00:31:35,060 --> 00:31:38,250
as Tai Lung wins each level, he
extinguishes all red light behind him.

528
00:31:38,764 --> 00:31:43,014
So that was one of the big,
overriding conceits for the sequence.

529
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:46,568
And hopefully, if we make you believe
the physics and the gravity

530
00:31:47,038 --> 00:31:50,498
of all the stuff with Tai Lung
in the hand-to-hand,

531
00:31:51,042 --> 00:31:54,141
you'll accept that he can defy
the laws of gravity in the end,

532
00:31:54,646 --> 00:31:58,566
when he starts to run back up
the falling debris.

533
00:31:59,184 --> 00:32:01,644
Which is obviously a complete
and utter cheat,

534
00:32:02,053 --> 00:32:05,653
but it is designed to show
how amazingly skillful he is.

535
00:32:06,224 --> 00:32:08,974
We should call out sound designers
who did an incredible job.

536
00:32:09,428 --> 00:32:11,008
Ethan Van der Ryn and Erik Aadahl.

537
00:32:11,296 --> 00:32:15,636
They approached this like King Kong,
Transformers and Lord of the Rings.

538
00:32:16,968 --> 00:32:21,158
Gave us a really amazing,
huge, epic soundtrack.

539
00:32:21,807 --> 00:32:23,767
We really wanted to bring them in,

540
00:32:24,109 --> 00:32:27,418
as we did with many of our other
creative people on our team,

541
00:32:27,946 --> 00:32:31,015
to say let's make this a real movie,
let's try to push the boundaries

542
00:32:31,516 --> 00:32:33,766
of what a family animated film can be.

543
00:32:34,152 --> 00:32:37,282
The first time we get to hear lan
McShane's voice come out of Tai Lung,

544
00:32:37,789 --> 00:32:40,219
and we realize he's actually a thinking,

545
00:32:40,625 --> 00:32:44,495
a very smart, and real being,
not just a feral beast.

546
00:32:45,096 --> 00:32:48,086
That was a conscious choice,
to have him not say anything

547
00:32:48,567 --> 00:32:52,287
until he's beaten his challenge.

548
00:32:52,871 --> 00:32:55,891
The only thing you would hear
would be actual animal sounds,

549
00:32:56,374 --> 00:32:58,304
you might think he was just bestial.

550
00:32:58,643 --> 00:33:02,743
lan is one of the most amazing actors.
He made our joke completely redundant.

551
00:33:03,381 --> 00:33:04,811
"Could I get a cup of tea, love?"

552
00:33:05,083 --> 00:33:07,193
He comes in as
the nicest guy in the world.

553
00:33:07,552 --> 00:33:10,242
And then, every single take,

554
00:33:10,689 --> 00:33:13,379
from A through Z,

555
00:33:13,825 --> 00:33:17,165
he'll find every single possible way
of delivering a line.

556
00:33:17,696 --> 00:33:21,535
And when he's finished he just looks
at you through the control room glass,

557
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:23,863
and goes, "Did I miss anything, love?"

558
00:33:24,169 --> 00:33:27,239
And you'll go, "No. No, that was great.
Let's move on."

559
00:33:27,739 --> 00:33:29,959
Nails it every time. Brilliantly.

560
00:33:30,342 --> 00:33:33,622
Halfway through production, we were
really trying to find Tai Lung.

561
00:33:35,080 --> 00:33:39,179
l was looking back at
The Hero with a Thousand Faces,

562
00:33:39,818 --> 00:33:42,338
and it talks about

563
00:33:42,754 --> 00:33:44,563
a villain is the hero of his own story.

564
00:33:44,890 --> 00:33:46,730
And that's perfect for Tai Lung,

565
00:33:47,058 --> 00:33:51,158
because he thinks he's been
unjustly imprisoned for 20 years.

566
00:33:51,796 --> 00:33:54,546
He wants that Dragon Scroll,
that's his third act.

567
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,340
In his mind, he's going
to get that scroll,

568
00:33:57,736 --> 00:34:00,456
everything's going to be great
and people will understand.

569
00:34:00,906 --> 00:34:05,036
And finally, he'll be able to be
the hero the way he wants it to be.

570
00:34:05,677 --> 00:34:08,487
Reconciliation of the father,
Shifu is the father figure.

571
00:34:08,947 --> 00:34:12,957
And I think that's
not interesting unless...

572
00:34:13,585 --> 00:34:15,804
Unless there's a human component
to the villain

573
00:34:16,187 --> 00:34:17,587
that makes you understand

574
00:34:17,856 --> 00:34:20,986
why they believe they're justified
in their villainy.

575
00:34:21,493 --> 00:34:23,273
We actually freaked people out.

576
00:34:23,594 --> 00:34:26,814
Then we kept getting the note:
"He's too dimensional. Too human.

577
00:34:27,331 --> 00:34:28,641
There's too much going on."

578
00:34:28,900 --> 00:34:31,040
I've got too much sympathy
for Tai Lung.

579
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:34,422
There's a balance we had to strike.
We wanted you to engage with him.

580
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:36,335
And believe him as a villain.

581
00:34:36,608 --> 00:34:39,418
At the same time, we didn't
want him to be totally sympathetic.

582
00:34:39,878 --> 00:34:43,248
That's why we ended up putting in
an abstracted version of a massacre

583
00:34:43,782 --> 00:34:46,362
in the flashback scene,
which will be coming up.

584
00:34:47,652 --> 00:34:51,252
Because people felt bad for Tai Lung.

585
00:34:51,822 --> 00:34:54,103
He wanted something
and he was denied it,

586
00:34:54,492 --> 00:34:56,862
locked away in
this hideous prison for 20 years.

587
00:34:57,262 --> 00:34:59,752
So we realized we hadn't
done a good enough job of

588
00:35:00,165 --> 00:35:04,085
justifying why Tai Lung
had to be incarcerated.

589
00:35:04,703 --> 00:35:08,333
So we put in this abstracted version
of him running amok

590
00:35:08,907 --> 00:35:10,517
in the Valley.

591
00:35:14,679 --> 00:35:18,159
So, we wanted Tai Lung
to cast a literal shadow

592
00:35:18,717 --> 00:35:20,767
over the second act of the movie,

593
00:35:21,119 --> 00:35:22,109
and also the Valley.

594
00:35:22,320 --> 00:35:23,988
We weren't going to cut to him
traveling back from the prison,

595
00:35:23,989 --> 00:35:25,419
We weren't going to cut to him
traveling back from the prison,

596
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:28,590
so we worked on the transition
from his escape

597
00:35:29,060 --> 00:35:30,549
into this next sequence.

598
00:35:30,829 --> 00:35:32,059
So that subliminally,

599
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:35,867
his shadow burns
over the landscape of the Valley,

600
00:35:37,268 --> 00:35:39,378
to indicate his coming threat.

