00:42:06,724 --> 00:42:09,004
And Alessandro Carloni
did an amazing job

716
00:42:09,394 --> 00:42:13,584
of animating the subtlety in this scene
of Shifu's amazing kung fu hearing.

717
00:42:14,232 --> 00:42:15,602
Disturbing his meditation.

718
00:42:15,867 --> 00:42:19,467
Also, in that opening shot, you'll see
the pressure of blue on negative color,

719
00:42:20,038 --> 00:42:23,818
pressing down on Shifu's
little bubble of warmth,

720
00:42:24,409 --> 00:42:27,539
which is about to be popped
by the news from Zeng.

721
00:42:28,046 --> 00:42:30,326
It's a big thing in a movie,
.
any movie,

722
00:42:30,715 --> 00:42:32,716
but particularly in a family film,

723
00:42:32,717 --> 00:42:33,147
but particularly in a family film,

724
00:42:33,284 --> 00:42:36,594
to make the decision
to kill off a character.

725
00:42:37,121 --> 00:42:41,401
When we knew that it was going to be
good for the story to do that,

726
00:42:42,060 --> 00:42:44,840
it actually changed
a lot of the tone of the film.

727
00:42:45,296 --> 00:42:47,576
It meant that we were going
to have to be...

728
00:42:47,965 --> 00:42:51,685
- It got deeper, it got richer.
- You can't do that in a trivial film.

729
00:42:52,270 --> 00:42:56,020
But he knows Shifu's struggling, he's
seen Shifu struggling for many years.

730
00:42:56,607 --> 00:42:59,327
Like a great therapist,
he doesn't ever give the answers.

731
00:42:59,777 --> 00:43:01,067
He's always gently guiding.

732
00:43:01,312 --> 00:43:04,442
I think this is a moment where
we like to think it's very clear

733
00:43:04,949 --> 00:43:07,879
that right here Oogway
makes his decision to leave,

734
00:43:08,352 --> 00:43:11,042
because he knows that Shifu
isn't going to be able to do it

735
00:43:11,489 --> 00:43:15,209
as long as Oogway's around
to be a crutch and to be relied on.

736
00:43:15,793 --> 00:43:17,433
Oogway knows "It is my time."

737
00:43:17,728 --> 00:43:20,538
Oogway chooses this departure time,
I'm getting goosebumps.

738
00:43:20,998 --> 00:43:24,278
It's a beautiful, emotional moment.
A significant moment in the story.

739
00:43:24,802 --> 00:43:28,022
I think it was one
of those sequences early on that

740
00:43:28,539 --> 00:43:32,609
was a real proof of concept for how deep
and emotional a movie could be.

741
00:43:33,244 --> 00:43:36,234
And how we wanted to make something

742
00:43:36,714 --> 00:43:38,703
that was taking the story seriously.

743
00:43:39,050 --> 00:43:41,950
We didn't want to be a parody, a spoof,
we didn't want to be jokey,

744
00:43:42,420 --> 00:43:45,930
we wanted to be significant
and deep and rich.

745
00:43:46,491 --> 00:43:49,421
And our actors,
Randall Duk Kim and Dustin

746
00:43:49,894 --> 00:43:52,524
we really asked them to dig in
for the sequence,

747
00:43:52,964 --> 00:43:55,334
to make it heartfelt,
to make it believable.

748
00:43:55,733 --> 00:43:58,453
Dustin had to be anguished
and conflicted.

749
00:43:58,903 --> 00:44:02,973
- And Randall had to be...
- Calm. At peace.

750
00:44:03,608 --> 00:44:05,358
.. accepting of...

751
00:44:05,676 --> 00:44:08,486
For Oogway this is an adventure,
it's not a bad thing,

752
00:44:08,946 --> 00:44:10,645
that he's moving on.

753
00:44:10,948 --> 00:44:13,348
There's a more interesting
adventure awaiting him

754
00:44:13,751 --> 00:44:17,061
on some other plane of existence.

755
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:20,368
He's OK with it.
It's Shifu who's very not OK

756
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:24,305
with losing his mentor, his master,
and his safety net, really,

757
00:44:24,862 --> 00:44:27,002
for everything that's about to come.

758
00:44:27,365 --> 00:44:29,884
And also, there's some back-story where

759
00:44:30,301 --> 00:44:34,371
Oogway knows that Shifu's destiny
is to be the next Oogway,

760
00:44:35,006 --> 00:44:38,546
and I think Shifu spent
a lot of his young career

761
00:44:39,110 --> 00:44:41,510
probably hoping to be
the Dragon Warrior himself.

762
00:44:41,913 --> 00:44:43,663
It wasn't until

763
00:44:43,981 --> 00:44:47,611
he believed he failed, he wasn't good
enough, didn't believe in himself,

764
00:44:48,186 --> 00:44:51,316
which is thematic to the film,
that he became a teacher.

765
00:44:51,822 --> 00:44:55,042
And he thought "I'm going to raise,
create the next Dragon Warrior,"

766
00:44:55,560 --> 00:44:58,020
Shifu's been on this track of
"l failed at my mission."

767
00:44:58,429 --> 00:45:01,039
Oogway's known, "No, there is a
greater mission for you."

768
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:04,565
Which is where Oogway
gives him his staff and says...

769
00:45:05,069 --> 00:45:06,649
"You're now me.

770
00:45:06,938 --> 00:45:09,248
You need to take over the role of..."

771
00:45:09,640 --> 00:45:12,450
Which Shifu doesn't get.
Shifu doesn't understand.

772
00:45:12,910 --> 00:45:14,870
He's using it as a weapon.

773
00:45:15,213 --> 00:45:19,053
He'll actually go on to use the staff
in a forceful way that is

774
00:45:19,650 --> 00:45:20,960
very strange.

775
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:43,772
And now we come to the sequence
we cursed early on in production,

776
00:45:43,774 --> 00:45:43,854
And now we come to the sequence
we cursed early on in production,

777
00:45:43,941 --> 00:45:45,750
by naming it "Fun in the Kitchen."

778
00:45:46,077 --> 00:45:47,417
The sequence is not fun.

779
00:45:47,678 --> 00:45:49,198
It actually is fun now.

780
00:45:49,480 --> 00:45:53,460
For many years it was
the absolute opposite of fun,

781
00:45:54,085 --> 00:45:57,425
It was the least funny sequence
you've ever seen.

782
00:45:57,955 --> 00:46:00,995
The core idea of Shifu,
after the death of his master,

783
00:46:01,492 --> 00:46:05,212
finding Po doing something ridiculous,

784
00:46:05,796 --> 00:46:09,196
that was the core idea, to have Shifu
coming from this horrible thing

785
00:46:09,734 --> 00:46:11,433
into everybody laughing,

786
00:46:11,736 --> 00:46:14,316
the Furious Five with their feet
up on the tables, eating,

787
00:46:14,739 --> 00:46:16,959
they're breaking their kung fu diet.

788
00:46:17,341 --> 00:46:20,560
We wanted to have the reality
come slamming into Po.

789
00:46:21,078 --> 00:46:23,067
And actually, I think it was Phil Craven

790
00:46:23,414 --> 00:46:27,134
who first boarded the idea that Po
makes fun of Shifu.

791
00:46:27,718 --> 00:46:29,798
And we expanded on that.

792
00:46:30,154 --> 00:46:31,584
So, Po starts imitating Shifu.

793
00:46:31,856 --> 00:46:33,876
I think it's brilliantly animated.

794
00:46:34,225 --> 00:46:37,475
It's mocking, but if
you listen carefully,

795
00:46:37,995 --> 00:46:41,065
he's making fun of himself.
He's using Shifu as the vehicle,

796
00:46:41,565 --> 00:46:43,935
but he's actually being
self-deprecating.

797
00:46:44,335 --> 00:46:47,055
And I think that's one of
the great things about Jack

798
00:46:47,505 --> 00:46:51,345
and Jack's performance in this. He's
never lashing out at anyone but himself.

799
00:46:51,942 --> 00:46:54,312
It's this consistent thing that he does.

800
00:46:54,712 --> 00:46:57,522
And because we needed this to be fun,

801
00:46:57,982 --> 00:47:00,412
we have the famous joke:
"The boob bowls."

802
00:47:02,219 --> 00:47:05,119
The biggest laugh
in the movie usually is...

803
00:47:05,589 --> 00:47:06,849
Back in the day!

804
00:47:07,091 --> 00:47:11,721
It used to be this sustained laugh
that would just go on and on.

805
00:47:12,430 --> 00:47:15,089
- Much to our surprise.
- We test screened to kids,

806
00:47:15,533 --> 00:47:18,493
and kids went nuts, they laughed
for a minute straight.

807
00:47:18,969 --> 00:47:22,449
And actually we should put that
soundtrack on the DVDs as an Easter egg.

808
00:47:23,007 --> 00:47:25,587
They laughed for a minute straight,
the craziest thing.

809
00:47:26,010 --> 00:47:29,490
They were climbing over the seats,
talking to their friends about it.

810
00:47:30,648 --> 00:47:32,988
And Jeffrey Katzenberg
was at that screening.

811
00:47:33,384 --> 00:47:35,404
l remember him turning
and looking at us.

812
00:47:35,753 --> 00:47:37,683
There was no way
we were cutting that scene.

813
00:47:38,022 --> 00:47:39,132
It's there forever.

814
00:48:13,190 --> 00:48:15,650
This next sequence was
the hardest one to get right.

815
00:48:16,060 --> 00:48:19,980
We knew we had this big comedic laugh
coming when we see Po running away.

816
00:48:20,598 --> 00:48:23,118
But the drama between these guys
and what gets said,

817
00:48:23,534 --> 00:48:26,494
in this moment of sheer panic
on Po's part,

818
00:48:26,971 --> 00:48:28,841
and truly it's panic on Shifu's part,

819
00:48:29,173 --> 00:48:31,162
he's made this commitment to Oogway,

820
00:48:31,509 --> 00:48:33,699
and he doesn't know how
he's going to pull it off.

821
00:48:34,078 --> 00:48:36,298
We did many versions of this sequence.

822
00:48:36,680 --> 00:48:38,850
This scene existed as a card.

823
00:48:39,216 --> 00:48:41,966
There was always a scene
we had to have in the film

824
00:48:42,420 --> 00:48:44,150
called "Po and Shifu have it out."

825
00:48:44,455 --> 00:48:48,674
Jed Diffenderfer did the earliest
version when it involved a punching bag.

826
00:48:49,326 --> 00:48:51,696
It was more of a training sequence.

827
00:48:52,096 --> 00:48:55,756
We went through so many versions
of trying to get this scene right.

828
00:48:56,333 --> 00:48:58,703
It was the last sequence
we put into production.

829
00:48:59,103 --> 00:49:01,413
We knew that because
we were having such trouble

830
00:49:01,806 --> 00:49:05,266
trying to get the balance right,
it would be the last thing we did.

831
00:49:05,810 --> 00:49:08,270
We recorded it more times
than any other scene,

832
00:49:08,679 --> 00:49:09,939
with Jack and Dustin.

833
00:49:10,181 --> 00:49:11,991
Jack was always like,
"This one again?"

834
00:49:12,316 --> 00:49:14,716
"Didn't I do this great already?"
And he always did.

835
00:49:15,119 --> 00:49:18,139
And it was us, we kept monkeying
with it, changing the writing

836
00:49:18,622 --> 00:49:20,202
and trying to change the status.

837
00:49:20,491 --> 00:49:23,481
Shift is the status transaction between
these two characters.

838
00:49:23,961 --> 00:49:26,330
Po, who was desperate to stay,

839
00:49:26,730 --> 00:49:29,510
who now is desperate to leave,
he knows his life's in danger.

840
00:49:29,967 --> 00:49:32,547
Shifu, who's made this commitment
to his master,

841
00:49:32,970 --> 00:49:36,629
who is committed to having Po stay
and trying to believe in him,

842
00:49:37,208 --> 00:49:39,578
and so they've flipped places here.

843
00:49:39,977 --> 00:49:43,957
Getting the actual chemistry and
balance right was very challenging.

844
00:49:44,582 --> 00:49:47,241
And also finding this no-man's-land
to set this in.

845
00:49:47,685 --> 00:49:49,825
It's not the dojo, it's not the palace,

846
00:49:50,187 --> 00:49:51,917
it's this area near the peach tree,

847
00:49:52,223 --> 00:49:55,093
so we're reminded of Oogway
in this spot,

848
00:49:55,559 --> 00:49:58,689
but, really it's a moment
where these two characters

849
00:49:59,196 --> 00:50:03,006
bare their souls and reveal their
deepest, darkest flaws.

850
00:50:03,601 --> 00:50:06,791
Po reveals that he doesn't
believe that he can do it.

851
00:50:07,304 --> 00:50:08,884
That this was all just a lark and...

852
00:50:09,173 --> 00:50:11,283
Shifu reveals that
he doesn't know how to do it,

853
00:50:11,642 --> 00:50:13,692
even though he has
committed to believing...

854
00:50:14,044 --> 00:50:16,794
These characters need each other
to complete their journey.

855
00:50:17,248 --> 00:50:19,028
They need each other so bad...

856
00:50:19,350 --> 00:50:21,980
But they don't know how
it's going to work at this point.

857
00:50:22,419 --> 00:50:24,379
- So this is their...
- It's a giving up.

858
00:50:24,722 --> 00:50:27,502
ina sense, emotionally,
this is their darkest point.

859
00:50:28,425 --> 00:50:30,295
And then Tigress will
pick up the charge.

860
00:50:30,628 --> 00:50:32,998
And that is always
what we wanted to have.

861
00:50:33,397 --> 00:50:36,327
That we saw the fracture
earlier in the kitchen,

862
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:38,500
when the Furious Five know...

863
00:50:38,802 --> 00:50:41,902
And she makes a plea to Shifu,
"Come on, give me my shot.

864
00:50:42,406 --> 00:50:45,866
Let me do it. I'm your best student,
we're all trained.

865
00:50:46,410 --> 00:50:47,779
You equipped us to do this."

866
00:50:48,045 --> 00:50:51,445
I think she's completely shaken

867
00:50:51,982 --> 00:50:55,732
when he rejects her
‘cause of his promise to Oogway.

868
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:58,810
She's defying her master,
she's defying Oogway,

869
00:50:59,223 --> 00:51:01,413
going against everything
she's ever learned.

870
00:51:01,792 --> 00:51:04,692
She's the most disciplined,
honorable of all warriors,

871
00:51:05,162 --> 00:51:08,672
and also at this moment
we get to see how amazing she is.

872
00:51:09,233 --> 00:51:11,513
And so we want the audience
to believe that

873
00:51:11,902 --> 00:51:14,272
- Tigress is going to do it.
- She's going to succeed.

874
00:51:14,672 --> 00:51:17,252
- They're going to join up.
- Like a team of superheroes.

875
00:51:17,675 --> 00:51:20,695
We want you to think, obviously,

876
00:51:21,178 --> 00:51:24,607
this crack elite force going out
to take down the bad guy,

877
00:51:25,149 --> 00:51:27,259
has got a huge chance of success.

878
00:51:28,619 --> 00:51:31,459
This location and moment
is affectionately known as

879
00:51:31,922 --> 00:51:33,472
"Mopey Mountain" to our crew.

880
00:51:33,757 --> 00:51:37,037
Mike Mitchell coined that term because
we used to have one more instance

881
00:51:37,561 --> 00:51:41,311
of Shifu sitting upset
and not sure what to do.

882
00:51:41,899 --> 00:51:44,558
And we pared it down
and went for the simpler one moment

883
00:51:46,637 --> 00:51:48,477
of despair before enlightenment.

884
00:51:48,806 --> 00:51:51,586
And that comes in the sound.

885
00:51:52,042 --> 00:51:55,612
Talking about the sound, yes, Shifu has
kung fu hearing, we established that,

886
00:51:56,180 --> 00:51:59,839
theoretically he should know
where the sound is coming from,

887
00:52:00,417 --> 00:52:03,877
and not go to the room
to see if Po's there,

888
00:52:04,421 --> 00:52:07,051
he should know where it's coming from,
but it worked better

889
00:52:07,491 --> 00:52:10,681
for him to go to the place
he expects it be,

890
00:52:11,195 --> 00:52:14,855
which is the training hall, and then to
find that Po's actually in the kitchen.

891
00:52:15,432 --> 00:52:18,622
It's actually very symbolic
for Shifu because

892
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:21,766
he's spent his whole life
thinking he knows the answer,

893
00:52:22,206 --> 00:52:23,786
he knows the right way to do things.

894
00:52:24,074 --> 00:52:26,704
He thinks those sounds should be
coming out of the dojo,

895
00:52:27,144 --> 00:52:30,743
this is the beginning of Shifu starting
to look at things a different way.

896
00:52:31,315 --> 00:52:33,455
Starting to think outside his box.

897
00:52:33,817 --> 00:52:35,807
His box is the training hall.

898
00:52:38,822 --> 00:52:42,542
He had to hit rock bottom in order
to be able to be aware enough,

899
00:52:43,127 --> 00:52:47,377
have his eyes open enough, to see that
Po can do things in a different way.

900
00:52:48,032 --> 00:52:50,932
This moment right here,
when he sees Po in the splits...

901
00:52:51,402 --> 00:52:54,682
Harking back to that split
that Tigress did in combat,

902
00:52:55,205 --> 00:52:58,305
Shifu says "It takes years to get
that right." Po can get that right

903
00:52:58,809 --> 00:53:02,029
when he's not thinking about it,
if he's thinking about something else.

904
00:53:02,546 --> 00:53:05,356
Po has this internal ability,
this natural ability,

905
00:53:05,816 --> 00:53:08,805
because of his love for kung fu,
his obsession with it.

906
00:53:09,286 --> 00:53:12,886
And it only can show itself
when he's distracted.

907
00:53:13,457 --> 00:53:15,386
Now we get to see him
distracted by food.

908
00:53:34,578 --> 00:53:37,678
This is part of Shifu's rebirth,
and re-inspiration as a teacher.

909
00:53:38,182 --> 00:53:41,252
He takes him outside of his box,
the training hall,

910
00:53:41,752 --> 00:53:45,382
to our equivalent
of Wudang Mountain in China.

911
00:53:47,091 --> 00:53:48,171
Avery mystical place,

912
00:53:48,392 --> 00:53:50,881
home of many Taoist monasteries,

913
00:53:51,295 --> 00:53:54,045
and often the home
in martial arts movies,

914
00:53:54,498 --> 00:53:58,778
and stories of the place

915
00:53:59,436 --> 00:54:02,016
where kung fu reaches
its highest level.

916
00:54:02,973 --> 00:54:05,933
But it was really important for us
to take Shifu as a character,

917
00:54:06,410 --> 00:54:08,720
out of his normal, everyday life,

918
00:54:09,113 --> 00:54:10,953
and he is now changing,
it's a rebirth.

919
00:54:11,281 --> 00:54:13,331
He goes back to this place,

920
00:54:13,684 --> 00:54:15,204
This is the birthplace of kung fu.

921
00:54:15,486 --> 00:54:17,625
It's where Oogway invented it,
taught Shifu,

922
00:54:17,988 --> 00:54:21,678
Shifu went and created
the box, the dojo,

923
00:54:22,259 --> 00:54:24,629
and started creating
a fabricated version of this.

924
00:54:25,028 --> 00:54:27,167
This is a very significant moment
for Shifu,

925
00:54:27,531 --> 00:54:30,461
to start turning this corner,
becoming more like Oogway,

926
00:54:30,934 --> 00:54:33,214
more open to the possibilities
of the universe.

927
00:54:33,604 --> 00:54:36,823
Then we get to see Oogway doing kung fu,
which is so cool.

928
00:54:37,341 --> 00:54:39,921
You'll see there's a lot
of lighting stuff in here.

929
00:54:43,013 --> 00:54:45,563
The scene starts
with being pretty misty,

930
00:54:45,983 --> 00:54:49,263
‘cause Po's in the fog,
he doesn't know where this is going.

931
00:54:49,787 --> 00:54:53,707
And then it transitions to
the sun breaking through.

932
00:54:54,324 --> 00:54:58,244
Which is back to our use of gold
as a heroic motif

933
00:54:58,862 --> 00:55:03,372
for the flashback to Oogway
at the point where he invented kung fu.

934
00:55:04,067 --> 00:55:07,547
Also for Shifu's symbolic rebirth

935
00:55:08,105 --> 00:55:10,065
and his declaration
that he is Po's master.

936
00:55:10,407 --> 00:55:13,247
That he is invested and invigorated,

937
00:55:13,710 --> 00:55:15,790
committed to making Po a success

938
00:55:16,146 --> 00:55:19,396
on the same place
where Oogway created kung fu.

939
00:55:19,917 --> 00:55:23,167
This is a great example of...
we didn't try to reinvent the genre.

940
00:55:23,687 --> 00:55:26,676
There's a training montage
in every sports movie,

941
00:55:27,157 --> 00:55:30,667
and every great kung fu origin film.

942
00:55:31,228 --> 00:55:33,808
A great hero training.

943
00:55:34,231 --> 00:55:36,981
So we're going to find
our version of that.

944
00:55:37,434 --> 00:55:38,834
We're not going to reinvent it,

945
00:55:39,102 --> 00:55:42,562
we're certainly not going to do
a really long one 'cause

946
00:55:43,106 --> 00:55:46,566
we wanted to show you this unlocking
happened over a long period of time,

947
00:55:47,110 --> 00:55:50,590
that it's believable, that at the end,
Po has unlocked all these abilities.

948
00:55:51,148 --> 00:55:54,168
We don't know exactly how long
it takes, it doesn't really matter.

949
00:55:54,651 --> 00:55:57,841
- Don't do the math, people.
- It doesn't make sense.

950
00:55:58,355 --> 00:56:00,905
It's just the idea that they went away,

951
00:56:01,325 --> 00:56:05,245
and they took as long as it took
for Po to get where he needed to go.

952
00:56:28,051 --> 00:56:29,831
We're coming to the chopstick fight,

953
00:56:30,153 --> 00:56:33,312
which is, hands down, the audience
favorite at every screening.

954
00:56:33,824 --> 00:56:37,394
It's the concept sequence that,
when we first executed it,

955
00:56:37,961 --> 00:56:40,921
everybody knew that this
was the film in a nutshell.

956
00:56:41,398 --> 00:56:44,028
The great relationship
between Po and Shifu.

957
00:56:44,468 --> 00:56:47,718
And this sequence actually started
many years ago.

958
00:56:48,238 --> 00:56:52,368
Rodolphe Guenoden had boarded it
as a fight between Tai Lung and Shifu.

959
00:56:53,010 --> 00:56:55,060
It was a contained fight
at a dinner table.

960
00:56:55,412 --> 00:56:58,922
It was a James Bond meets
the supervillain thing,

961
00:56:59,483 --> 00:57:02,913
They were being polite to each other as
they talked about their back-story,

962
00:57:03,453 --> 00:57:06,063
but trying to dominate
each other as they...

963
00:57:07,691 --> 00:57:10,531
...tried to steal food out of each
other's chopsticks.

964
00:57:10,994 --> 00:57:14,684
Then we realized that Po's training
was going to be food-based,

965
00:57:15,265 --> 00:57:17,455
we remembered and brought
that sequence back,

966
00:57:17,834 --> 00:57:22,553
a story artist named Phil Craven,
who was trained by Rodolphe in story.

967
00:57:23,273 --> 00:57:25,353
- How very apt.
- Yeah.

968
00:57:25,709 --> 00:57:27,408
He took the sequence and made it new,

969
00:57:27,711 --> 00:57:30,231
and actually exploded it
and made the epic version.

970
00:57:30,647 --> 00:57:32,817
So it starts very small and goes big.

971
00:57:33,183 --> 00:57:35,203
Phil did, I think, an amazing job.

972
00:57:35,552 --> 00:57:38,742
He boarded the previous sequence, too.
The training montage.

973
00:57:39,256 --> 00:57:41,366
Giving us this believable arc

974
00:57:41,725 --> 00:57:44,505
from the panda who doesn't
know how to do anything,

975
00:57:44,962 --> 00:57:47,132
to the panda who manages to figure out

976
00:57:47,497 --> 00:57:51,156
how to unlock and use his abilities
by the end of the sequence.

977
00:57:51,735 --> 00:57:55,135
What was really cool, was when Jack saw
the finished movie he pointed out

978
00:57:55,672 --> 00:57:59,832
he didn't realize how layered and
significant some of these moments were.

979
00:58:00,477 --> 00:58:04,227
So the "I'm not hungry" moment
really resonated and plays great.

980
00:58:04,815 --> 00:58:07,245
We get applause in some of
our audience screenings.

981
00:58:07,651 --> 00:58:10,020
Again, the chopstick fight

982
00:58:12,723 --> 00:58:16,703
had a lot of very careful thought
in the visual design of that sequence.

983
00:58:17,327 --> 00:58:21,137
Again, it's lit with gold light.

984
00:58:21,732 --> 00:58:25,302
We don't have any
conventional skies in our film

985
00:58:25,869 --> 00:58:28,619
until our very last sequence,
the end with the credits.

986
00:58:29,806 --> 00:58:33,176
A very deliberate choice, every sky
is there for an emotional reason.

987
00:58:33,710 --> 00:58:36,370
That one was a bright yellow sky

988
00:58:37,848 --> 00:58:40,978
because it's Po's becoming a hero.

989
00:58:42,119 --> 00:58:44,989
Also, there's a lot of red in the trees.

990
00:58:45,455 --> 00:58:46,355
Again, our power color.

991
00:58:46,356 --> 00:58:46,876
Again, our power color.

992
00:58:47,024 --> 00:58:50,334
So, the mix of those color elements
became a significant thing

993
00:58:50,861 --> 00:58:53,201
in the visual design of that sequence.

994
00:58:53,597 --> 00:58:57,347
And now we're coming up to one of the
biggest set pieces in our film,

995
00:58:57,934 --> 00:59:00,594
one of the coolest, most ambitious...

996
00:59:01,038 --> 00:59:03,288
This sequence took forever
to figure out,

997
00:59:03,673 --> 00:59:05,752
not only how to do
this particular sequence,

998
00:59:06,109 --> 00:59:09,679
but what this sequence was going to be,
it was another one of those scenes

999
00:59:10,247 --> 00:59:12,767
we knew we had to have the Five
fight Tai Lung.

1000
00:59:13,183 --> 00:59:16,173
So, love the way lan McShane

1001
00:59:16,653 --> 00:59:19,493
plays Tai Lung

1002
00:59:19,956 --> 00:59:21,506
when he's talking to Tigress.

1003
00:59:21,792 --> 00:59:24,922
Here, the bridge is being cut.
Basically they're both in danger

1004
00:59:25,429 --> 00:59:28,299
of being plummeted
into this bottomless abyss.

1005
00:59:28,765 --> 00:59:31,984
And he's so nonchalant
and self-possessed.

1006
00:59:32,502 --> 00:59:35,372
The artists did a great job
of just having him lean.

1007
00:59:37,107 --> 00:59:38,717
Jed came up with that image.

1008
00:59:39,009 --> 00:59:41,289
There he is, he doesn't care.

1009
00:59:41,678 --> 00:59:44,897
that he's thousands of feet
above a bottomless precipice.

1010
00:59:45,415 --> 00:59:47,935
He can afford to be comfortable
and relaxed,

1011
00:59:48,351 --> 00:59:51,421
he's cool enough to even
walk along the tightrope

1012
00:59:51,922 --> 00:59:54,882
without blinking
or breaking into a sweat.

1013
00:59:55,358 --> 00:59:57,938
And lan just plays
this moment perfectly.

1014
00:59:58,361 --> 01:00:01,520
That Tai Lung hears Po's name
for the first time

1015
01:00:02,032 --> 01:00:03,702
and conjures up

1016
01:00:04,568 --> 01:00:07,818
this, obviously, completely
incorrect image in his head,

1017
01:00:08,338 --> 01:00:10,968
that he's got a worthy opponent

1018
01:00:11,408 --> 01:00:13,428
waiting for him at the end of his road,

1019
01:00:13,777 --> 01:00:17,237
which will be the completion
of Tai Lung's hero story.

1020
01:00:17,781 --> 01:00:21,731
That Tai Lung actually bests this guy
who's worthy of his skill.

1021
01:00:22,352 --> 01:00:25,781
Certainly, this is
the most technically challenging

1022
01:00:26,323 --> 01:00:27,553
and complex sequence.

1023
01:00:27,791 --> 01:00:31,041
The dynamics of figuring out
the rope bridge moving constantly...

1024
01:00:31,561 --> 01:00:33,141
The breakage of the boards.

1025
01:00:33,430 --> 01:00:36,359
Characters adjusting their weight
on the bridge as it's moving.

1026
01:00:36,833 --> 01:00:39,083
The mist is also super-complicated.

1027
01:00:39,469 --> 01:00:42,979
Hopefully none of this is self-evident.
You should be caught up in the action.

1028
01:00:43,540 --> 01:00:45,850
But when we were brainstorming about

1029
01:00:46,243 --> 01:00:48,433
what was going to be the venue

1030
01:00:48,812 --> 01:00:52,322
for this epic fight
between the Five and Tai Lung.

1031
01:00:52,883 --> 01:00:56,453
When the idea was proposed to the
special effects people,

1032
01:00:57,020 --> 01:01:01,330
that it was going to be on a shifting,
crumbling, breaking rope bridge,

1033
01:01:01,992 --> 01:01:05,472
they all went ashen and white
and looked really scared.

1034
01:01:06,029 --> 01:01:10,219
And we thought, "Great! Perfect.
We don't know how to do that."

1035
01:01:10,867 --> 01:01:14,677
- So that means it's worth trying.
- Nobody's ever done it before.

1036
01:01:15,272 --> 01:01:17,172
It's obviously really hard
to figure out.

1037
01:01:17,507 --> 01:01:21,727
And really, just to give you
an idea of how complicated it is,

1038
01:01:22,379 --> 01:01:25,949
Viper, which is the most complicated
character in our film,

1039
01:01:26,516 --> 01:01:29,296
just because she has
so many points of articulation,

1040
01:01:29,753 --> 01:01:32,443
she's a very complicated rig to work.

1041
01:01:32,889 --> 01:01:35,579
And the bridge is,
essentially, four Vipers.

1042
01:01:36,026 --> 01:01:39,455
Because there's four major ropes
to the structure of the bridge.

1043
01:01:39,996 --> 01:01:41,426
Just to give you an idea of how

1044
01:01:41,698 --> 01:01:44,658
complicated it is
for the animators to deal with.

1045
01:01:45,135 --> 01:01:47,065
Love Jen's idea

1046
01:01:47,404 --> 01:01:49,894
of not seeing Tai Lung

1047
01:01:50,307 --> 01:01:51,616
as he flips off the rope.

1048
01:01:51,875 --> 01:01:54,045
The rope kind of like attached to

1049
01:01:54,411 --> 01:01:57,191
the shark in Jaws
plowing through the mist.

1050
01:01:57,647 --> 01:01:59,607
Tai Lung is so good, he's so quick,

1051
01:01:59,950 --> 01:02:03,350
that you don't even see him
when he does his kung fu spring.

1052
01:02:03,887 --> 01:02:04,220
So, in keeping with

1053
01:02:04,221 --> 01:02:05,951
So, in keeping with

1054
01:02:06,256 --> 01:02:08,625
the idea that Tai Lung is the hero
of his own story,

1055
01:02:09,025 --> 01:02:12,535
even though he's mostly in cool colors.

1056
01:02:13,096 --> 01:02:15,376
We've kept his eyes golden,
our hero color.

1057
01:02:15,765 --> 01:02:18,924
And we used the transition
from the gold of his eyes

1058
01:02:19,436 --> 01:02:23,776
to the gold of the sunset here,

1059
01:02:24,441 --> 01:02:26,961
because Tai Lung
has beat these five masters.

1060
01:02:27,377 --> 01:02:28,747
In his eyes,

1061
01:02:29,012 --> 01:02:32,292
he is on his journey to be
the Dragon Warrior.

1062
01:02:32,816 --> 01:02:35,006
And this is another step in his story,

1063
01:02:35,385 --> 01:02:39,895
where he is the hero and he has
defeated the overwhelming odds.

1064
01:02:40,590 --> 01:02:45,250
We wanted to play the drama of they've
been paralyzed and defeated by Tai Lung,

1065
01:02:45,962 --> 01:02:49,422
but we wanted the comedy as well
of the fact that

1066
01:02:49,966 --> 01:02:52,046
these guys are now incapacitated.

1067
01:02:52,402 --> 01:02:55,592
And Po has to figure out
how he's going to...

1068
01:02:56,106 --> 01:02:58,796
Now he's left, he's the only solution
to this problem.

1069
01:02:59,242 --> 01:03:02,522
We wanted to basically freak Po out
as much as possible

1070
01:03:03,046 --> 01:03:05,915
by seeing the evidence of what Tai Lung
has done to the Five.

1071
01:03:15,058 --> 01:03:17,398
So, we go into

1072
01:03:17,794 --> 01:03:20,513
a very, very difficult
and lengthy scene,

1073
01:03:20,964 --> 01:03:23,074
that was very hard to get right.

1074
01:03:23,433 --> 01:03:25,423
There was a lot this scene
had to accomplish.

1075
01:03:25,769 --> 01:03:27,939
There were a lot of story points
that had to land,

1076
01:03:28,305 --> 01:03:31,815
a lot of emotional turns,
a lot of things that had to happen.

1077
01:03:32,375 --> 01:03:35,335
And so we knew we were
trying to pack it all in.

1078
01:03:37,347 --> 01:03:41,067
The movie's been building up to this
moment of Po getting this Dragon Scroll.

1079
01:03:41,651 --> 01:03:44,401
The opening of the Ark of
the Covenant, it's this huge moment.

1080
01:03:44,854 --> 01:03:47,343
It's the moment that Shifu and Po

1081
01:03:47,757 --> 01:03:52,737
believe is actually going to make
everything turn out OK.

1082
01:03:53,496 --> 01:03:55,196
Po thinks he's going to be transformed.

1083
01:03:55,498 --> 01:03:58,518
Shifu is taking steps towards
becoming more like Oogway.

1084
01:03:59,002 --> 01:04:01,962
By using the staff, he's showing that

1085
01:04:02,439 --> 01:04:06,828
he's using Oogway's staff to get
the Scroll in this way,

1086
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:10,610
That shows he's changing from being the

1087
01:04:11,114 --> 01:04:14,014
harsh taskmaster, the kung fu trainer,

1088
01:04:14,484 --> 01:04:18,614
to being the more enlightened
and involved character.

1089
01:04:19,255 --> 01:04:21,625
He's still hardcore,
the thing we wanted to have.

1090
01:04:22,025 --> 01:04:24,395
This contrast, this combination of Shifu

1091
01:04:24,794 --> 01:04:26,933
doing something in a hardcore way
with kung fu,

1092
01:04:27,297 --> 01:04:30,337
but he's redirecting these petals
just on wafts of air.

1093
01:04:30,834 --> 01:04:33,674
Also worth noting, not something most
people would register,

1094
01:04:34,137 --> 01:04:38,417
but it is actually the first time Shifu
calls Po by name.

1095
01:04:39,075 --> 01:04:40,625
As opposed to calling him Panda.

1096
01:04:40,910 --> 01:04:43,600
Which indicates how far
their relationship has come.

1097
01:04:44,047 --> 01:04:47,067
He's no longer an object,
he's a person.

1098
01:04:47,550 --> 01:04:49,890
He's a friend,
that there is genuine affection.

1099
01:04:50,286 --> 01:04:52,686
This is the key scene for Shifu's arc.

1100
01:04:53,089 --> 01:04:56,719
Here's a guy who was almost trying
to kill this guy in the beginning,

1101
01:04:57,293 --> 01:05:00,863
drive him away, beat him up, detested
him, wanted him out of his sight.

1102
01:05:01,698 --> 01:05:04,357
And in this scene he actually

1103
01:05:04,801 --> 01:05:07,701
has come so far that he's prepared
to lay down his life

1104
01:05:08,171 --> 01:05:12,511
to give this guy a chance
to fulfill his destiny.

1105
01:05:13,176 --> 01:05:18,216
It's where a lot of
the elements of the film come,

1106
01:05:18,982 --> 01:05:21,762
also, it's got a big reversal,

1107
01:05:22,218 --> 01:05:26,118
obviously when the scroll
is revealed to be blank.

1108
01:05:26,723 --> 01:05:28,653
We've been building up the entire movie,

1109
01:05:28,992 --> 01:05:31,362
it's been a thousand years
of history in this world

1110
01:05:31,761 --> 01:05:34,221
that this scroll contains a secret,

1111
01:05:34,631 --> 01:05:36,330
The secret to limitless power.

1112
01:05:36,633 --> 01:05:39,473
The thing throughout production,

1113
01:05:39,936 --> 01:05:41,196
we tried many things.

1114
01:05:41,438 --> 01:05:43,548
Early on in the story we had

1115
01:05:43,907 --> 01:05:47,887
the scroll was, at times,
the Dragon's sword,

1116
01:05:48,511 --> 01:05:51,851
locked in a room we never saw.

1117
01:05:52,382 --> 01:05:54,432
It was a box that had something in it.

1118
01:05:54,784 --> 01:05:56,834
"The greatest power
in any of us is within."

1119
01:05:57,187 --> 01:05:59,467
You open the box, it's empty.
We put a mirror in it.

1120
01:05:59,856 --> 01:06:02,106
We tried many different versions
knowing that

1121
01:06:02,492 --> 01:06:05,272
this was the philosophical idea

1122
01:06:05,728 --> 01:06:07,158
we wanted to deliver.

1123
01:06:07,430 --> 01:06:10,649
But it took us a while
to find the exact means to deliver it.

1124
01:06:11,167 --> 01:06:12,717
And then once we figured it out,

1125
01:06:13,002 --> 01:06:14,872
everything fell into place around it.

1126
01:06:15,205 --> 01:06:18,775
It's also worth noting, this is
a particularly lovely run of music

1127
01:06:19,342 --> 01:06:23,382
from this sequence into the next,

1128
01:06:24,013 --> 01:06:25,743
through the end of the movie.

1129
01:06:26,049 --> 01:06:29,389
This little ramp of music
that Hans and John did

1130
01:06:29,919 --> 01:06:32,229
is particularly gorgeous

1131
01:06:32,622 --> 01:06:35,872
and supports all the emotions
in the scene.

1132
01:06:37,293 --> 01:06:38,783
We love the way the music works.

1133
01:06:49,839 --> 01:06:50,839
And then we go into
the big transition into our exodus.

1134
01:06:50,840 --> 01:06:52,800
And then we go into
the big transition into our exodus.

1135
01:06:53,142 --> 01:06:54,752
Brilliantly done by Yong Duk,

1136
01:06:55,044 --> 01:06:58,734
this use of succession of cuts
through the long lens.

1137
01:06:59,315 --> 01:07:02,625
‘Cause we don't want to make it
feel like there was...

1138
01:07:03,152 --> 01:07:04,962
We wanted to find that...

1139
01:07:05,288 --> 01:07:08,308
Not too much panic. We didn't want
bloodcurdling screams.

1140
01:07:08,791 --> 01:07:11,511
We wanted there to be
an intensity and energy.

1141
01:07:11,961 --> 01:07:14,071
There's definitely
an imperative to get out

1142
01:07:14,430 --> 01:07:16,450
before the bogeyman returns.

1143
01:07:16,799 --> 01:07:18,969
Most of the energy comes from camera.

1144
01:07:19,335 --> 01:07:20,295
The handheld camera.

1145
01:07:20,503 --> 01:07:24,453
Especially in contrast to how stately
the previous sequence has been.

1146
01:07:25,074 --> 01:07:26,244
It really worked well.

1147
01:07:26,476 --> 01:07:30,346
That's the Shaw brothers there,
two other members of Tenacious D,

1148
01:07:30,947 --> 01:07:33,907
- they're stealing a foo dog.
- Our favorite dumb joke in the movie.

1149
01:07:34,384 --> 01:07:36,694
Nobody sees it and it goes by quickly.

1150
01:07:37,086 --> 01:07:39,015
Little red wagon
with a giant stone foo dog,

1151
01:07:39,355 --> 01:07:43,135
that's the thing they've chosen to try
and rescue as they get out of town.

1152
01:07:43,726 --> 01:07:45,276
They're morons.

1153
01:07:45,562 --> 01:07:48,551
One of our way-homers.
It always made us happy.

1154
01:07:49,032 --> 01:07:52,602
And then, when we get into
Po reuniting with his dad,

1155
01:07:53,169 --> 01:07:56,038
this sequence was done
by Alessandro Carloni

1156
01:07:57,807 --> 01:08:01,116
he came up with the joke of the dad
putting the apron back on Po.

1157
01:08:01,644 --> 01:08:04,663
It's a brilliant piece
of visual storytelling.

1158
01:08:05,148 --> 01:08:08,488
For Po's dad, nothing has changed,
everything's back where it should be,

1159
01:08:09,018 --> 01:08:11,768
Po's going to come back
to the kitchen, he's oblivious,

1160
01:08:12,221 --> 01:08:13,831
he's tying Po back into his old life.

1161
01:08:14,123 --> 01:08:17,313
But then, when we get into
the emotional content later,

1162
01:08:17,827 --> 01:08:19,997
you notice the dad
isn't oblivious, he is aware.

1163
01:08:20,363 --> 01:08:24,313
That was really important for us to not
continuously play the dad for comedy,

1164
01:08:24,934 --> 01:08:28,244
but to let there be
a significant relationship here.

1165
01:08:28,770 --> 01:08:31,291
That doesn't always get talked about.

1166
01:08:33,076 --> 01:08:35,626
His dad really does love Po.

1167
01:08:38,481 --> 01:08:41,441
I think the very nice piece of
storytelling that's very sweet

1168
01:08:41,917 --> 01:08:44,548
is that the dad's only way
of trying to heal his son,

1169
01:08:44,988 --> 01:08:49,028
make him feel better is to use
the thing the dad loves the most,

1170
01:08:49,658 --> 01:08:51,709
he loves noodles more than anything.

1171
01:08:52,060 --> 01:08:55,460
He hopes that by
expressing that to his son,

1172
01:08:55,999 --> 01:08:58,278
that this will make his son better.

1173
01:08:58,667 --> 01:09:01,037
He's trying to heal his son
by giving him...

1174
01:09:01,437 --> 01:09:03,017
The only thing he's got left.

1175
01:09:03,305 --> 01:09:06,495
.. the most amazing thing in the world,
