01:10:04,333 --> 01:10:06,413
And then literally,
in the blink of an eye,

1195
01:10:06,769 --> 01:10:10,109
since we've established
that Tai Lung can appear

1196
01:10:10,640 --> 01:10:12,310
like the bogeyman out of nowhere.

1197
01:10:12,608 --> 01:10:14,828
And we think Tai Lung waited

1198
01:10:15,211 --> 01:10:17,521
until Shifu blinked
in the lightning flash,

1199
01:10:17,914 --> 01:10:20,103
to choose to make his appearance there.

1200
01:10:20,483 --> 01:10:22,623
We wanted to create
tension in this moment,

1201
01:10:22,985 --> 01:10:26,644
This very still, static camera
face off moment.

1202
01:10:27,223 --> 01:10:29,533
The electricity in the air
of the building storm

1203
01:10:29,926 --> 01:10:32,266
before the storm breaks.

1204
01:10:32,662 --> 01:10:35,972
With these two guys, everything
is subtext in this conversation.

1205
01:10:36,499 --> 01:10:39,429
Twenty years of... everything, actually.

1206
01:10:39,902 --> 01:10:43,442
There's not just a lot of hatred there,

1207
01:10:44,006 --> 01:10:47,466
there's also love and regret.

1208
01:10:48,010 --> 01:10:50,090
There's a great amount
of depth in this story.

1209
01:10:50,446 --> 01:10:54,606
This is when all the pieces come
together, now we get the last flashback.

1210
01:11:14,637 --> 01:11:17,097
There's a significant,
emotional turning point

1211
01:11:17,507 --> 01:11:20,166
that exists in this sequence.

1212
01:11:20,610 --> 01:11:23,240
It used to be much longer
and more significant.

1213
01:11:25,581 --> 01:11:27,331
If you notice, if you look closely,

1214
01:11:27,650 --> 01:11:30,370
Shifu is defending in the whole
beginning part of the fight.

1215
01:11:30,820 --> 01:11:34,160
Defending, defending and
it's not until Tai Lung finds

1216
01:11:34,690 --> 01:11:37,059
Shifu's staff,

1217
01:11:37,460 --> 01:11:40,070
finds Cogway's staff over at his shrine,

1218
01:11:40,496 --> 01:11:42,046
over near the candles,

1219
01:11:42,331 --> 01:11:44,471
that Tai Lung realizes
that Oogway is gone.

1220
01:11:44,834 --> 01:11:46,943
That it truly is between him and Shifu.

1221
01:11:47,303 --> 01:11:50,113
He asks Shifu, "Give me the Scroll,"
basically is the subtext.

1222
01:11:50,573 --> 01:11:53,593
This is the first time Shifu goes on
the attack and attacks his son.

1223
01:11:54,076 --> 01:11:58,326
Because he's defiled the memory
of Oogway by touching his staff.

1224
01:12:09,692 --> 01:12:13,092
And the breaking of the staff
became a significant one,

1225
01:12:13,629 --> 01:12:17,199
in the land of Shifu's journey
to becoming Oogway,

1226
01:12:17,767 --> 01:12:20,397
and the staff becoming a symbol

1227
01:12:20,837 --> 01:12:23,057
of Oogway's wisdom and benignness,

1228
01:12:23,439 --> 01:12:26,779
but is now used as a weapon
with Tai Lung trying to kill Shifu.

1229
01:12:27,310 --> 01:12:30,090
So it's being used in
this completely negative way.

1230
01:12:30,546 --> 01:12:34,006
And we made the choice to make breaking
the staff a somewhat magical event.

1231
01:12:34,550 --> 01:12:37,100
There's a life-force inside that staff.

1232
01:12:37,520 --> 01:12:39,630
It's the last part of Oogway,

1233
01:12:39,989 --> 01:12:41,888
when that staff is broken

1234
01:12:42,225 --> 01:12:44,855
and that light is snuffed out
within the staff,

1235
01:12:45,294 --> 01:12:47,814
we see the last echo of Oogway,

1236
01:12:48,231 --> 01:12:51,691
the petals that are left
around the moon pool blow across,

1237
01:12:52,235 --> 01:12:56,214
and that distracts Shifu long enough
for Tai Lung to get in this sucker kick.

1238
01:12:56,839 --> 01:12:59,799
Not a sucker punch, but a sucker kick
that pounds him into the wall.

1239
01:13:02,078 --> 01:13:05,298
Shifu's running for his life
for the rest of the sequence.

1240
01:13:06,849 --> 01:13:10,479
When they breakout through the roof
of the palace,

1241
01:13:11,053 --> 01:13:13,803
there was some discussion about
whether we needed to do that.

1242
01:13:14,257 --> 01:13:17,717
Maybe that was more fight
than was necessary.

1243
01:13:18,261 --> 01:13:21,011
But, Mark and I fought
very hard to keep it in.

1244
01:13:21,464 --> 01:13:24,504
We felt it added a legendary

1245
01:13:25,001 --> 01:13:28,601
and epic quality to the conflict
between the father and the son,

1246
01:13:29,171 --> 01:13:32,301
to have them burst out into the sky
against a crack of lightning.

1247
01:13:34,977 --> 01:13:37,876
It was a very important part
of the fight,

1248
01:13:38,347 --> 01:13:42,126
to take it outside for
the final drop back into the fire.

1249
01:13:53,729 --> 01:13:55,979
And I think it's all about
going more and more epic.

1250
01:13:56,365 --> 01:13:57,855
We wanted this to increase...

1251
01:13:59,201 --> 01:14:02,041
completely turning up
the volume of this battle.

1252
01:14:02,505 --> 01:14:03,438
So that we could, in contrast,

1253
01:14:03,439 --> 01:14:04,369
So that we could, in contrast,

1254
01:14:04,573 --> 01:14:07,643
get the funniest battle
to come on the heels of it.

1255
01:14:08,144 --> 01:14:11,624
Yeah, they sort of become
Greek gods at that point.

1256
01:14:12,181 --> 01:14:15,281
Shifu and Tai Lung fighting in the sky.

1257
01:14:16,485 --> 01:14:20,384
And then when Po returns,
like we were mentioning,

1258
01:14:20,990 --> 01:14:22,800
the new light coming back in,

1259
01:14:23,125 --> 01:14:25,435
and the likeness tonally
to the story comes back,

1260
01:14:27,897 --> 01:14:29,947
Po knows the secret, he understands

1261
01:14:30,299 --> 01:14:33,429
but he has no idea
how he's going to win this fight.

1262
01:14:33,936 --> 01:14:36,835
He just knows he has to save Master
Shifu by distracting Tai Lung.

1263
01:14:37,306 --> 01:14:40,085
The one thing Tai Lung wants
is the scroll.

1264
01:14:40,543 --> 01:14:43,643
The thing Tai Lung wants more
than anything in the world

1265
01:14:44,146 --> 01:14:46,135
is the power he believes
is in that scroll.

1266
01:14:46,482 --> 01:14:49,522
Which we all know is nothing.
But, Tai Lung doesn't know that.

1267
01:14:50,019 --> 01:14:52,509
What's interesting here
is Po is using the scroll,

1268
01:14:52,922 --> 01:14:54,531
he's relying on an artificial...

1269
01:14:54,824 --> 01:14:58,013
he's still relying on
an external thing to gain the advantage,

1270
01:14:58,527 --> 01:15:01,927
so Po hasn't become enlightened yet.
We save that for later.

1271
01:15:02,465 --> 01:15:05,305
He's still relying on Tai Lung's
desire for the scroll

1272
01:15:05,768 --> 01:15:09,168
and using that against him. But that
gives us somewhere to go in the fight

1273
01:15:09,705 --> 01:15:11,665
so we can have more shape to it.

1274
01:15:12,008 --> 01:15:13,998
This conceit for the fight,

1275
01:15:14,343 --> 01:15:17,473
with the using of the scroll,
was a little

1276
01:15:17,980 --> 01:15:21,549
Muhammad Ali‘Cassius Clay,
Joe Frazier,

1277
01:15:22,118 --> 01:15:26,278
the rope-a-dope, where Po's
wearing Tai Lung down,

1278
01:15:26,922 --> 01:15:31,262
as Tai Lung renews his efforts
to try and get the scroll.

1279
01:15:31,927 --> 01:15:34,007
He's using his weaknesses against him.

1280
01:15:34,363 --> 01:15:37,763
- He knows Tai Lung wants the scroll
- Emotionally, he wearing Tai Lung down.

1281
01:15:38,300 --> 01:15:41,960
He knows the clincher is going to be
when Tai Lung opens the scroll.

1282
01:15:42,538 --> 01:15:46,197
And understands that Po doesn't have
any special magic powers,

1283
01:15:46,776 --> 01:15:49,526
he's been bested by a panda.

1284
01:15:50,579 --> 01:15:53,919
That's the most humiliating thing.
This Panda is standing up to him.

1285
01:15:54,450 --> 01:15:57,880
This whole sequence now is the ultimate
callback to the chopstick fight.

1286
01:15:58,421 --> 01:16:01,881
We've seen the game of keep away
and how effective that was.

1287
01:16:02,425 --> 01:16:05,325
So Po is using that training
he got from Shifu,

1288
01:16:05,795 --> 01:16:08,075
to do the ultimate game
of keep away with Tai Lung.

1289
01:16:08,464 --> 01:16:12,064
We spent a lot of time wondering what
the shape of this battle would to be.

1290
01:16:12,635 --> 01:16:16,325
We'd had epic fights, the Shifu-Tai Lung
fight, the bridge fight,

1291
01:16:16,906 --> 01:16:20,416
and so we were wondering
how big and crazy

1292
01:16:20,976 --> 01:16:23,696
does this final fight have to be?
Do we set it in a volcano or

1293
01:16:24,146 --> 01:16:27,606
what's the legendary setting that we're
going to have for this final battle?

1294
01:16:28,150 --> 01:16:32,019
We realized Po's journey has
taken him from his noodle shop

1295
01:16:32,621 --> 01:16:35,611
up to the world of kung fu
in the Jade Palace.

1296
01:16:36,092 --> 01:16:40,312
And so what we needed to do
was retrace his steps.

1297
01:16:40,963 --> 01:16:42,803
Take him back from the palace,

1298
01:16:43,132 --> 01:16:45,562
in fact, the fight ends up at the door

1299
01:16:45,968 --> 01:16:48,718
of the noodle restaurant.

1300
01:16:49,171 --> 01:16:52,131
So we took it back through all
the places that Po had been,

1301
01:16:52,608 --> 01:16:55,128
and re-incorporated ideas
we had seen in the film,

1302
01:16:55,544 --> 01:16:58,674
now being repurposed by Po
in a different way.

1303
01:16:59,181 --> 01:17:03,311
To use them as an effective battle
against Tai Lung.

1304
01:17:03,953 --> 01:17:06,613
Whether it was the fireworks or

1305
01:17:07,056 --> 01:17:09,955
the idea of the chopstick battle,
now used with woks.

1306
01:17:10,426 --> 01:17:13,206
And we're coming up
on the most dramatic...

1307
01:17:15,131 --> 01:17:17,711
Tai Lung has taken out
his aggression on Po,

1308
01:17:18,134 --> 01:17:20,534
and is desiring the scroll,
he practically kills Po.

1309
01:17:20,936 --> 01:17:22,456
He creates a crater around him.

1310
01:17:22,738 --> 01:17:24,818
A circular crater,
circular language again.

1311
01:17:25,174 --> 01:17:26,784
Tai Lung gets the scroll.

1312
01:17:28,377 --> 01:17:30,217
The most important thing for us is,

1313
01:17:30,546 --> 01:17:33,126
this battle could have
gone on for decades,

1314
01:17:33,549 --> 01:17:37,359
we joked at one point
this would go on for two years...

1315
01:17:37,953 --> 01:17:41,613
- The legendary battle.
- ...across the mountains of China.

1316
01:17:42,191 --> 01:17:44,971
And we decided it was more significant
to end the battle here

1317
01:17:45,427 --> 01:17:46,687
outside the noodle shop.

1318
01:17:46,929 --> 01:17:49,619
Give this moment,
which was a truly heroic moment,

1319
01:17:50,065 --> 01:17:53,525
as Po, the noble warrior,
offers the answer to Tai Lung.

1320
01:17:55,871 --> 01:17:58,211
If Tai Lung were
to accept that answer...

1321
01:17:58,607 --> 01:18:01,477
A shot at redemption if Tai Lung had
listened to Po's wisdom,

1322
01:18:01,944 --> 01:18:05,544
he might not get...
into oblivion at the end.

1323
01:18:06,115 --> 01:18:09,014
This is also the moment when
the playing field has been leveled.

1324
01:18:09,485 --> 01:18:11,915
Now the secret is out,
the scroll is meaningless.

1325
01:18:12,321 --> 01:18:15,721
And Po has to stand back up again
and fight without any advantage.

1326
01:18:16,258 --> 01:18:18,508
Truly use only himself

1327
01:18:18,894 --> 01:18:20,504
and what he has within himself,

1328
01:18:20,796 --> 01:18:23,016
to see how this fight's going to work.

1329
01:18:23,399 --> 01:18:27,589
It was important for the shape
of the fight to have that change occur,

1330
01:18:28,237 --> 01:18:31,427
where Po is now fighting with nothing
but his own skills, his own wits.

1331
01:18:31,941 --> 01:18:34,281
Everything he's learned from Shifu,

1332
01:18:34,677 --> 01:18:36,487
his body...

1333
01:18:36,812 --> 01:18:40,212
A lot of people have said
"Po's overweight."

1334
01:18:40,749 --> 01:18:44,029
He's not overweight. Po is exactly
the right weight for a panda.

1335
01:18:44,553 --> 01:18:47,163
And that's why he beats Tai Lung.

1336
01:18:47,590 --> 01:18:49,870
Po is the peach.

1337
01:18:50,259 --> 01:18:53,189
The soft, squishy peach
that Oogway was talking about.

1338
01:18:53,662 --> 01:18:56,322
His soft and squidginess,
his bounciness,

1339
01:18:56,765 --> 01:19:00,515
his absorbency, all the things we've
seen, where he bounces down stairs,

1340
01:19:01,103 --> 01:19:03,733
and can absorb all those things.

1341
01:19:04,173 --> 01:19:09,242
His ability to redirect Tai Lung's hard
force back against him,

1342
01:19:10,012 --> 01:19:11,621
using a martial art principle,

1343
01:19:11,914 --> 01:19:14,084
that allows him to win.

1344
01:19:14,450 --> 01:19:17,320
A mixture of some real martial arts

1345
01:19:17,786 --> 01:19:20,036
and some very Tex Avery stuff.

1346
01:19:20,422 --> 01:19:23,321
His most Tex Avery moment
in the whole movie,

1347
01:19:23,792 --> 01:19:26,662
the cookie cut-out hole
that Tai Lung has smashed into.

1348
01:19:27,129 --> 01:19:30,879
And what's great is we earned
the ability at this point

1349
01:19:31,467 --> 01:19:33,137
to be as silly as that,

1350
01:19:33,435 --> 01:19:36,245
as ridiculous as that, all the final
battle stuff we're doing,

1351
01:19:36,705 --> 01:19:39,195
because we've been
so grounded throughout.

1352
01:19:39,608 --> 01:19:41,778
And we allow ourselves
to get to this point

1353
01:19:42,144 --> 01:19:45,134
where Tai Lung can climb out of
that hole and be messed up

1354
01:19:45,614 --> 01:19:48,954
and be still on the attack to Po
and Po can get the advantage.

1355
01:19:49,485 --> 01:19:51,535
We had a lot of discussion about

1356
01:19:51,887 --> 01:19:54,376
what is the final thing
that's going to get...

1357
01:19:54,790 --> 01:19:56,220
How do we get rid of the villain?

1358
01:19:57,126 --> 01:19:58,966
We knew we had this
big fight Po would win,

1359
01:19:59,295 --> 01:20:02,297
but we didn't know how he was going
to win, what he was going to do.

1360
01:20:02,298 --> 01:20:02,527
but we didn't know how he was going
to win, what he was going to do.

1361
01:20:02,631 --> 01:20:05,881
We had a belly blast that
sent Tai Lung through 15 buildings

1362
01:20:06,402 --> 01:20:08,512
and he ended up in Po's bedroom.

1363
01:20:08,871 --> 01:20:12,591
And he looked up and saw all of
Po's fan stuff all over the walls

1364
01:20:13,175 --> 01:20:14,515
and was completely confused.

1365
01:20:14,777 --> 01:20:15,917
That didn't seem enough,

1366
01:20:16,145 --> 01:20:20,425
we were questing around
for the definitive final thing

1367
01:20:21,083 --> 01:20:23,133
that will get rid of our villain?

1368
01:20:23,485 --> 01:20:26,615
And we found the answer
was already in the movie.

1369
01:20:27,990 --> 01:20:29,599
Derek Dryman's Wuxi finger hold,

1370
01:20:29,892 --> 01:20:32,412
which we had implanted as

1371
01:20:32,828 --> 01:20:37,078
this formidable, ultimate, who knows
what happens when you drop your pinkie,

1372
01:20:37,733 --> 01:20:41,603
in the scene where
Shifu and Po first meet.

1373
01:20:42,204 --> 01:20:43,374
It was obvious,

1374
01:20:43,605 --> 01:20:45,945
or became obvious,
it wasn't obvious for a while,

1375
01:20:46,342 --> 01:20:48,362
it became a thing we discovered.

1376
01:20:48,711 --> 01:20:52,751
That we should see what happens
when you drop the pinkie.

1377
01:20:53,382 --> 01:20:56,861
And what happens when you drop
the pinkie is a mysterious,

1378
01:20:57,419 --> 01:20:59,229
and obviously somewhat magical event.

1379
01:20:59,555 --> 01:21:02,575
It harks back to
the circle language of the ripples,

1380
01:21:03,058 --> 01:21:06,078
and also to the Oogway energy

1381
01:21:06,562 --> 01:21:08,142
that he used in the nerve touches.

1382
01:21:08,430 --> 01:21:11,040
It's actually, in some versions of it,

1383
01:21:11,467 --> 01:21:14,897
when we were planning it, it ended up
looking like an atomic bomb explosion.

1384
01:21:15,437 --> 01:21:17,897
We made the choice that,
since this is probably

1385
01:21:18,307 --> 01:21:22,147
a really masterful kung fu technique,

1386
01:21:22,745 --> 01:21:24,474
it shouldn't look that destructive.

1387
01:21:24,780 --> 01:21:26,620
It should look magical and benign.

1388
01:21:26,949 --> 01:21:28,879
So we used golden light
and rings of energy

1389
01:21:29,218 --> 01:21:31,268
to hark back to

1390
01:21:31,620 --> 01:21:34,050
the water ripples in
Oogway's nerve touch.

1391
01:21:34,456 --> 01:21:36,356
Just on a gigantic scale.

1392
01:21:36,692 --> 01:21:38,652
We have no idea
what happened to Tai Lung,

1393
01:21:38,994 --> 01:21:40,804
it's one of the mysteries of the movie,

1394
01:21:41,130 --> 01:21:44,880
whether he's atomized,

1395
01:21:45,467 --> 01:21:46,987
or what actually happened to him.

1396
01:21:48,971 --> 01:21:51,960
Now we're coming up on my most
favorite part of the whole movie,

1397
01:21:52,441 --> 01:21:55,251
and it definitely gets
the best audience response,

1398
01:21:55,711 --> 01:21:59,991
this interchange between the dying Shifu

1399
01:22:00,649 --> 01:22:02,519
and the returning hero.

1400
01:22:04,520 --> 01:22:07,590
It's another cliched moment
that everyone expects.

1401
01:22:08,090 --> 01:22:10,310
The master's going to die.
Everyone expects that

1402
01:22:10,692 --> 01:22:14,152
we're going to follow suit with what you
would expect with this kind of movie.

1403
01:22:14,696 --> 01:22:17,006
And we get a great moment from Dustin

1404
01:22:17,399 --> 01:22:20,709
when it's revealed that even
in this moment of enlightenment,

1405
01:22:21,236 --> 01:22:23,456
he's the same guy,
he's still the same character,

1406
01:22:23,839 --> 01:22:27,179
and a character can only grow so much,
can only have so much insight,

1407
01:22:27,709 --> 01:22:30,579
and it's a really touching moment...

1408
01:22:31,713 --> 01:22:34,463
...emotionally, because not only
do we feel like he's dying,

1409
01:22:34,917 --> 01:22:38,137
but we get this great reversal and
it's such a joy that he's still alive!

1410
01:22:38,654 --> 01:22:40,174
We cheat unapologetically.

1411
01:22:40,456 --> 01:22:43,856
We told Dustin,
play it like you're dying.

1412
01:22:44,393 --> 01:22:46,613
So we make the audience think that.

1413
01:22:46,995 --> 01:22:50,945
Every time we've seen the film,
we've heard the audiences go, "Oh."

1414
01:22:51,567 --> 01:22:54,847
A little kid behind me said,
"Mommy, is Master Shifu dying?"

1415
01:22:55,370 --> 01:22:56,830
The mom said, "Yes he is, honey."

1416
01:22:57,105 --> 01:23:00,674
And then, when he was still alive,
there was a huge laugh.

1417
01:23:01,243 --> 01:23:03,523
The mom was shaking the kid,
"He's alive!"

1418
01:23:03,912 --> 01:23:07,342
He's still the same. So, just to go back
to the first time we saw Po,

1419
01:23:07,883 --> 01:23:09,492
he was upside down.

1420
01:23:09,785 --> 01:23:09,983
Here at the end of the movie,
he's back upside down.

1421
01:23:09,985 --> 01:23:12,474
Here at the end of the movie,
he's back upside down.

1422
01:23:12,888 --> 01:23:14,908
In a mix of gold for heroism

1423
01:23:15,257 --> 01:23:17,097
and green for wisdom.

1424
01:23:17,426 --> 01:23:19,506
He has completed his journey,

1425
01:23:19,862 --> 01:23:21,202
under his own terms.

1426
01:23:21,463 --> 01:23:23,893
And that says "Kung Fu Panda"
behind in the logo there.

1427
01:23:24,299 --> 01:23:26,049
The Chinese characters.

1428
01:23:26,368 --> 01:23:29,298
The idea here was we wanted
to bring back the 2-D

1429
01:23:29,771 --> 01:23:33,281
as a call back to
the dream sequence.

1430
01:23:33,842 --> 01:23:35,982
We wanted to give
the characters a curtain call

1431
01:23:36,345 --> 01:23:38,075
in this great graphic environment.

1432
01:23:39,615 --> 01:23:41,165
Book end the film

1433
01:23:41,450 --> 01:23:44,320
with the language we've established
for heroes in Po's mind.

1434
01:23:44,786 --> 01:23:47,246
The graphic, 2-D language.

1435
01:23:48,724 --> 01:23:52,854
Now Po has earned
his place in that world, too.

1436
01:23:53,829 --> 01:23:56,349
Plus, there's a lot of credits
in an animated film.

1437
01:23:56,765 --> 01:24:00,105
There's almost ten minutes of credit.
That's a lot real estate in the film,

1438
01:24:00,636 --> 01:24:04,556
which has a brief running time
like our film has.

1439
01:24:05,173 --> 01:24:07,393
So, we figured if we have
all that time,

1440
01:24:07,776 --> 01:24:11,556
we might as well use it to try
and do something fun and artistic.

1441
01:24:12,147 --> 01:24:15,307
Anybody who's watching the credits

1442
01:24:15,817 --> 01:24:17,867
they should be seeing
something beautiful.

1443
01:24:18,220 --> 01:24:20,910
Our 2-D animators, certainly our
3-D animators, on the show

1444
01:24:21,356 --> 01:24:23,755
actually got the chance
to do some 2-D animation.

1445
01:24:24,159 --> 01:24:26,558
All the shots you see of the characters

1446
01:24:26,962 --> 01:24:30,152
are done by a lot of our animators
who worked on the film.

1447
01:24:30,666 --> 01:24:33,766
So it was a great way for them
to return to their roots.

1448
01:24:34,269 --> 01:24:35,729
Flex that old 2-D muscle

1449
01:24:36,004 --> 01:24:38,634
that's been a little bit
underused recently.

1450
01:24:39,074 --> 01:24:41,914
But I think everyone
loves traditional animation.

1451
01:24:42,377 --> 01:24:44,927
It was great to not only get the movie
in there, but to have

1452
01:24:45,347 --> 01:24:47,456
our animators return
to their roots like that.

1453
01:24:47,816 --> 01:24:51,626
We also wanted to honor everybody
who worked so hard on this movie.

1454
01:24:52,220 --> 01:24:57,170
We wanted white type scrolling
against black for ten minutes.

1455
01:24:57,926 --> 01:25:00,146
Which was not interesting to look at.

1456
01:25:00,529 --> 01:25:03,399
We wanted to make sure people
were looking at the credits.

1457
01:25:03,865 --> 01:25:06,995
Seeing the names of everybody who worked
on the film and made it great.

1458
01:25:07,502 --> 01:25:09,232
And actually enjoying doing that.

1459
01:25:09,538 --> 01:25:10,998
‘Cause it was beautiful art.

1460
01:25:11,273 --> 01:25:13,263
We worked with a great company
called Shine,

1461
01:25:13,609 --> 01:25:16,359
who helped to execute
these end credits.

1462
01:25:16,812 --> 01:25:20,942
Working with Ramone and Tang, our
production designer and art director.

1463
01:25:21,583 --> 01:25:25,503
That combination of those guys
and Shine.

1464
01:25:28,423 --> 01:25:31,702
The sense that the story of our world
continues after this movie.

1465
01:25:32,894 --> 01:25:35,004
We didn't want to have
the storytelling end.

1466
01:25:36,298 --> 01:25:38,048
We have a definitive end to the movie,

1467
01:25:38,367 --> 01:25:40,707
but we wanted to give the audience

1468
01:25:41,103 --> 01:25:43,473
a little bit more time
with the characters.

1469
01:25:43,872 --> 01:25:46,532
And hint at some call backs.

1470
01:25:47,476 --> 01:25:51,165
We just wanted people to
enjoy the continuation.

1471
01:25:52,247 --> 01:25:54,327
Something Amir Zaki does
in a lot of his films

1472
01:25:54,683 --> 01:25:56,353
that we've found inspirational,

1473
01:25:56,652 --> 01:26:00,082
that sense that you just drop in
to see a story at a particular moment,

1474
01:26:00,622 --> 01:26:02,582
that world was there
before you got there,

1475
01:26:02,924 --> 01:26:05,824
and will continue afterwards,
we love that.

1476
01:26:06,294 --> 01:26:08,693
We thought it would be
an interesting thing to do

1477
01:26:09,097 --> 01:26:11,467
to try and indicate...

1478
01:26:12,734 --> 01:26:16,304
Those are these little vignettes, where
Po is still working in the noodle shop,

1479
01:26:16,872 --> 01:26:20,352
and his father is playing
mahjong with Shifu and winning.

1480
01:26:20,909 --> 01:26:24,249
Or that Tigress is having
a moment with Shifu

1481
01:26:24,780 --> 01:26:26,920
so that her story has improved.

1482
01:26:27,282 --> 01:26:28,652
Shifu's laughing.

1483
01:26:28,917 --> 01:26:32,817
And Tigress is able to have
a bit more sense of humor

1484
01:26:33,422 --> 01:26:34,712
than we've seen in the film.

1485
01:26:34,956 --> 01:26:37,176
All these little moments indicate

1486
01:26:37,559 --> 01:26:40,079
the world has changed
for the better.

1487
01:26:40,495 --> 01:26:42,394
It continues the way it always was.

1488
01:26:42,731 --> 01:26:45,191
Because that is what is so nice
about Po's story.

1489
01:26:45,600 --> 01:26:48,850
Is that he is basically the same guy
that he was in the beginning.

1490
01:26:49,371 --> 01:26:51,211
He's a little bit more of that guy.

1491
01:26:51,540 --> 01:26:55,170
Because he's allowing himself to take
his internal and make it external.

1492
01:26:55,744 --> 01:26:58,733
He is the Dragon Warrior, but
working at his father's restaurant.

1493
01:26:59,214 --> 01:27:01,384
serving noodles when
he's not saving the world.

1494
01:27:01,750 --> 01:27:05,120
And Shifu is still a little bit on edge.

1495
01:27:05,654 --> 01:27:07,904
He's trying to learn
to be like Oogway every day,

1496
01:27:08,290 --> 01:27:09,960
but he's still going to snap at Po.

1497
01:27:10,659 --> 01:27:14,529
His dad is still going to care
about noodles and love his son.

1498
01:27:15,130 --> 01:27:19,350
But everybody is hopefully... their
lives are just a little bit better.

1499
01:27:20,001 --> 01:27:23,951
A little bit more relaxed, they know a
little bit more about each other.

1500
01:27:24,573 --> 01:27:27,443
And hopefully we feel this world
that we're leaving

1501
01:27:27,909 --> 01:27:30,688
is left with everybody

1502
01:27:31,146 --> 01:27:32,755
knowing more about themselves.

1503
01:27:33,048 --> 01:27:34,947
That makes their lives better.

1504
01:27:35,283 --> 01:27:38,823
Po, the thing we want people to feel,
the thing we don't necessarily show

1505
01:27:39,387 --> 01:27:41,996
is that the world truly has changed
by Po's example.

1506
01:27:42,424 --> 01:27:44,734
Because everyone has seen

1507
01:27:45,127 --> 01:27:49,197
this most unlikely character
become a kung fu master.

1508
01:27:49,831 --> 01:27:52,111
Now they all hopefully will go back,

1509
01:27:52,501 --> 01:27:55,811
whatever they believe or want
for themselves, they can pursue it.

1510
01:27:56,338 --> 01:27:59,148
He's enlightened everyone.
Whether you're trying to be a chef

1511
01:27:59,608 --> 01:28:00,948
or an artist, whatever it is,

1512
01:28:01,209 --> 01:28:04,139
that Po's example
is the most extreme example.

1513
01:28:04,613 --> 01:28:06,603
And the most enlightened example.

1514
01:28:08,049 --> 01:28:09,889
If you look, there's a shot of Po

1515
01:28:10,218 --> 01:28:13,178
showing the children of the village,
these little rabbits,

1516
01:28:13,655 --> 01:28:16,905
the blank scroll,
so they can see their reflection.

1517
01:28:18,326 --> 01:28:21,426
For a thousand years
that secret has been withheld.

1518
01:28:21,930 --> 01:28:25,060
And it's for the world to see.
Po is not going to withhold it,

1519
01:28:25,567 --> 01:28:28,377
he's going to let everyone see it,
he let Tai Lung see it.

1520
01:28:28,837 --> 01:28:29,887
That was the lesson,

1521
01:28:30,105 --> 01:28:32,794
that Oogway had to wait
for somebody like Po

1522
01:28:33,241 --> 01:28:34,531
to come along to understand,

1523
01:28:34,776 --> 01:28:37,356
that a warrior wouldn't have
necessarily got there.

1524
01:28:37,779 --> 01:28:40,409
Po, not being a warrior,

1525
01:28:40,849 --> 01:28:43,839
but Po just being himself,
he does understand.

1526
01:28:44,319 --> 01:28:47,859
He's allowing everybody to see
their true potential.

1527
01:28:48,423 --> 01:28:50,293
And hopefully believe

1528
01:28:50,625 --> 01:28:53,375
that they can accomplish
whatever their dream might be.

1529
01:28:53,829 --> 01:28:56,228
Let's thank our editorial department.

1530
01:28:57,499 --> 01:28:59,079
it's not just post-production.

1531
01:28:59,367 --> 01:29:02,467
They truly are editing the movie
from the very beginning

1532
01:29:02,971 --> 01:29:05,160
and they are the last ones
to leave the project.

1533
01:29:05,907 --> 01:29:07,957
They're like the Marines.
First in, last out.

1534
01:29:08,310 --> 01:29:10,300
It's amazing.

1535
01:29:10,645 --> 01:29:14,625
There's never a break. We're always
building towards a screening,

1536
01:29:15,250 --> 01:29:16,830
some important deadline,

1537
01:29:17,118 --> 01:29:20,578
so they're always working around
the clock and on weekends.

1538
01:29:21,122 --> 01:29:22,322
I don't know how they do it.

1539
01:29:22,557 --> 01:29:24,637
So, to Clare Knight,

1540
01:29:24,993 --> 01:29:27,513
and CK Horness,
and Jeremy Shipp,

1541
01:29:27,929 --> 01:29:31,999
and everybody in editorial,
thank you.

1542
01:29:32,634 --> 01:29:34,854
There's no movie without you guys.

1543
01:29:35,237 --> 01:29:37,577
You worked like champs
to make this film happen.

1544
01:29:38,740 --> 01:29:42,809
And, of course, the other departments
that we should have mentioned,

1545
01:29:43,445 --> 01:29:44,785
that we didn't talk about,

1546
01:29:45,046 --> 01:29:46,826
we have Alex Parkinson,

1547
01:29:48,250 --> 01:29:50,090
he wore many hats on our show.

1548
01:29:50,418 --> 01:29:54,607
He did an amazing job of coordinating
many painstaking aspects of our film,

1549
01:29:55,257 --> 01:29:56,456
to make sure that

1550
01:29:56,691 --> 01:29:59,531
when we wanted a crowd scene,
we'd be able to have a crowd scene.

1551
01:29:59,995 --> 01:30:02,925
We'd have those details
and bits and pieces taken care of.

1552
01:30:03,398 --> 01:30:06,148
A lot of what those guys do
is invisible to most people,

1553
01:30:06,601 --> 01:30:09,851
because you just accept it
as being right and natural,

1554
01:30:10,372 --> 01:30:12,982
but, getting the cloth
to fall over the fur or

1555
01:30:13,408 --> 01:30:16,748
to get the crowd
to interact with each other,

1556
01:30:17,279 --> 01:30:20,469
and not collide or go through
or any of those things

1557
01:30:20,982 --> 01:30:23,612
that would totally break
your belief in the world,

1558
01:30:24,052 --> 01:30:26,982
were handled by Alex and his team

1559
01:30:27,455 --> 01:30:29,855
completely invisibly.

1560
01:30:30,258 --> 01:30:33,657
So you could just enjoy the story.
But they were incredibly difficult.

1561
01:30:34,195 --> 01:30:36,035
For the most part,

1562
01:30:36,364 --> 01:30:38,973
the clothing system was designed

1563
01:30:39,401 --> 01:30:42,771
to follow the characters and allow the
characters to move a lot.

1564
01:30:43,305 --> 01:30:46,235
There was so much hand animation
that had to occur

1565
01:30:46,708 --> 01:30:48,348
to make all the cloth look perfect.

1566
01:30:48,643 --> 01:30:52,153
I love this little moment where Po
has got an action figure of himself.

1567
01:30:52,714 --> 01:30:54,494
He's now carved his own action figure.

1568
01:30:54,816 --> 01:30:57,066
He's now, he really is
the theme of the movie,

1569
01:30:57,452 --> 01:30:59,152
which is: he is his own hero.

1570
01:30:59,454 --> 01:31:00,384
He's his own fan boy.

1571
01:31:00,588 --> 01:31:04,508
He's got his own model of himself
to prove it.

1572
01:31:05,126 --> 01:31:08,226
So, 1 want to talk about the cookie.

1573
01:31:08,730 --> 01:31:12,830
We didn't want it to be a joke.
We wanted it to be

1574
01:31:13,468 --> 01:31:16,488
an end of the story between
Po and Shifu.

1575
01:31:16,972 --> 01:31:19,112
Beautifully animated by Ben Willis.

1576
01:31:19,474 --> 01:31:22,784
They're friends and Po's question,
"Do you want to get something to eat?"

1577
01:31:23,311 --> 01:31:25,971
Well, yes they do and they're doing it
under the peach tree,

1578
01:31:26,414 --> 01:31:28,584
which is returning to life.

1579
01:31:28,950 --> 01:31:32,519
Weill see the new peach tree
is starting to sprout.

1580
01:31:33,088 --> 01:31:35,718
And we leave our heroes,
looking over the valley

1581
01:31:36,157 --> 01:31:39,527
as two friends,
under Oogway's peach tree.

1582
01:31:40,061 --> 01:31:43,021
For me, John Stevenson,
one of the directors of Kung Fu Panda.

1583
01:31:43,498 --> 01:31:45,607
- And...
- Mark Osborne, the other director,

1584
01:31:45,967 --> 01:31:47,637
we say thank you.

1585
01:31:47,936 --> 01:31:49,196
- Be your own hero.
- Yes.

1586
01:31:49,437 --> 01:31:52,337
And always, always,
look within for the answer.

